article.headline: Quinnipiac 80, Wagner 72
article.story: NEW YORK (AP) -- DeMario Anderson scored 25 points to help Quinnipiac beat Wagner 80-72 on Thursday night. Adam Gonzalez added 19 points, seven rebounds and six assists for the Bobcats (4-10, 2-3 Northeast). Victor Akinyanju also had 16 points and a career-high 17 rebounds. Mark Porter led the Seahawks (4-11, 1-3) with 22 points and James Ulrich added 14. With the game tied at 8, the Bobcats went on a 15-3 run to take a 23-11 advantage with 8:34 left in the half. They extended the margin to 40-27 at the break. Wagner could get no closer than 67-60 on Porter's 3-pointer with 3:11 in the game.
